URL =  https://www.commonsclause.com

== Description ==

Nathan Schneider:

"Heather Meeker represented MongoDB when it created the Server Side Public License in 2018.  The same year, she was part of the team that drafted the Commons Clause, an add-on to familiar Open Source licenses that converts them into “source available” licenses: the source code is open and available to all, but the right to commercialize the licensed software is not. A year later, Meeker led the development of the PolyForm Project, a website whose initial version offered five different software licenses for various business models; these include a “free trial” license and licenses that restrict use to noncommercial and small-business purposes, respectively."
(https://osf.io/hnerp/?view_only=44b5c10772d5470892b701dfe4b2c833)

